A simple toy to change the constant deceleration of a mouse in an easy GUI way.
It uses xinput to change the value of Constant Deceleration.

Created by Ukyoi.



== Compiling Guide ==

0. Make sure you have Qt 4 and qmake which fits your Qt version.
1. Open the directory on your terminal.
2. Run "qmake" (or alternatives on your distribution e.g. qmake-qt4 on Arch linux) to generate Makefile.
3. Run "make" to compile it.


== Using Guide ==

0. Compile it first.
1. Run the executable file (simpmouse).
2. Select your mouse on the list and set the value of Constant Deceleration.
3. Press Apply to apply the change.
